Text.Value: You certainly came out on top, didn't you? But I'm more than happy to take a slight loss on this particular transaction. I like you.
My favourite future clients. Are you ready to accept my kind offer?
No deal.
Of course.
Ha! Haha! Hahaha!
But of course. I could never allow such a festering pustule of a city to die - it's an object lesson in mortal excess.
Before the end comes, you'll find yourself in his presence again. When that happens, use the Hammer to shatter the chains that hold him.
Your prince awaits, githyanki. And the dawning of a new age.
Destiny waits in the wings. Find the brain, destroy it, and seize that Crown.
Now - I have business elsewhere. But rest assured, we'll talk again.
Still holding out hope for another solution?
I'll wait. You'll be back.
That was reckless. In a devil's hands, the crown could be as dangerous as any artefact in existence - we need to nullify the terms of that deal.

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyed, you didn't listen to him

Text.Value: Thanks, Raphael. You just helped to save Baldur's Gate.
*The ink has barely dried, yet you feel a growing disquiet at what exactly you just signed. Perhaps a diabolist can offer some comfort. Or a way out... for a devil's bargain is a hard one to break.*
And our deal depends on your contract. I'll keep it safe for you, in my House of Hope.
The pleasure's all mine - I got everything I wanted out of this.
You should have a little more faith.
Everything that ends, ends badly. You just bought a chance to ward off the ending for a little longer.
You will find yourself in Orpheus' presence before the end comes. When the moment comes, use the Hammer to shatter the chains that hold him.
My dear Karlach, I'm delighted you've seen sense. You'll find everything is in order.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Raphael gestures to his left, and a floating contract appears in a burst of flame, hovering
EditorData.VFXTags: [PK] Burst of Flames when the Contract appears

Text.Value: Remind me of the terms of the deal.
Ah, what fun we would've had if you'd tried.
Be sure to keep the Hammer safe until then. Your survival depends on it.
If you weren't my last fucking option, I'd rip your horns off.
Excellent, excellent. You'll find everything is in order.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Raphael gestures to his left, and a floating contract appears in a burst of flame, hovering
EditorData.VFXTags: [PK] Burst of Flames when the Contract appears

Text.Value: And this agreement will bring us both what we want. You'll save your world, I'll unite the hells. And the illithids will be eradicated.
You give me the Crown once you have destroyed the elder brain.
To do that, we'll need to find a diabolist willing to open a backdoor to the hells, sneak into Raphael's home, and destroy the contract. Simple.

EditorData.NodeContext: annoyed that all of this is necessary because of a bad choice the player made. Outlining an impossible plan and finishing on that very sarcastic 'simple'.

Text.Value: How do I use the Hammer to free Orpheus?
A pleasure doing business with you.
I give you the Orphic Hammer, the means by which Prince Orpheus of the githyanki can be freed from his chains.
Are you sure about this?

EditorData.NodeContext: Fear and worry in her voice. Player has just said they want to sign a contract with Raphael

Text.Value: I still expect this to end badly.
Let's sign the contract.

Synopsis: Stub for Raphael after the "Tango" scene, where Raphael suggested the contract to the player. The player may reconsider later on.
